abstract: Space Exploration Technologies Corporation's Falcon 9 rocket booster safely returns to earth 10 minutes after launching in Cape Canaveral, Fla; SpaceX hopes to refurbish and relaunch rocket, effort that would greatly reduce cost of traveling to space.
lead_paragraph: The launch and landing could become a familiar sight in spaceflight, allowing rockets to be refurbished and reused.

headline.main: SpaceX Successfully Lands Rocket After Launch of Satellites Into Orbit
headline.print_headline: Space Firm Lands Rocket as Planned After Launch
